By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  Lagos state top the COVID-19 chat with 316 cases and FCT came second with 210 infections as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control recorded 1,041 new cases in the country. Other states where new infections were reported are as follows: Kaduna-83, Plateau-70, Gombe and Oyo-56 each, Katsina-47, Nasarawa-35, Kano-33, Ogun-21, Rivers-17, Niger and Imo-14 each, Delta, Kwara, and Edo- 12 each, Benue-9, Anambra-8, Ebonyi-6, Taraba and Ekiti-4 each, Bayelsa and Sokoto-1each. According to the report released via it’s twitter handle late Thursday, the total confirmed cases have risen to 81,963 out of which 69,651 patients have been treated and discharged from various isolation facilities in the country. The health agency also informed that 1,242 lives been lost to COVID-19 related ailments since the index case was reported in February 2020. See the breakdown of total confirmed cases below: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Nigeria on Saturday recorded 110 new cases of COVID-19 infections, bringing the total confirmed cases in the country to 67,330, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has said. This is also as the Centre has informed that a total of 62,819 patients have… November 29, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Precise Post) -   The national health agency in charge of COVID-19, Nigeria Centre for  Disease Control on Tuesday announced the confirmation of 296 new cases of the novel virus in the country. The agency reported that the new infections were recorded in 15 states of the… September 9, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The total confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Nigeria hit 59,001 as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) reported 153 new fresh infections on Thursday. Similarly, the NCDC report released via it's twitter handle account further said that the total of 50, 452… October 2, 2020 In "Top Stories"